 political turbulence, such as the rise of ISIL, Russia’s incursions into Ukraine and the Brexit vote in the United Kingdom. Others explore the secret places not shown on Google Earth or reflect fast-changing landscapes. Beyond the Map journeys out into a world of mysterious, daunting and magical spaces. It is a world of hidden cultures and ghostly memories, of uncountable new islands and curious stabs at paradise. From the phantom tunnels of the Tokyo subway to a stunning movie-set re-creation of 1950s-era Moscow; from the caliphate of the Islamic State to virtual cybertopias—this book serves as an imaginative guide to the farthest fringes of geography.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aCuriosities and wonders. 0aGeographyvMiscellanea. 7aTravel / General.2bisacsh  aenclave, lands, utopia, expansion, social studies, geography, professor, school, teacher, student, educational, college, academic, scholarly, analysis, climate change, islands, ocean, pollution, environmental, environment, gardens, international, air conditions, cultural, religious, political, interdisciplinary, research, travel, wanderlust, adventure, contemporary, modern day, isil, russia, ukraine, brexit, united kingdom, landscape, tunnels, tokyo, japan, google earth, cyber.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311068858040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226513980423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226513980/original  a978-3-11-068858-0  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles